                            <comment id="13551144" author="dsiegel@knewton.com" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2013 14:49:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve looked through the source for Thrift 0.6.1 and found the following endian-ness values used when reading/writing doubles:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Java TBinaryProtocol: Big Endian&lt;br/&gt;
Java TCompactProtocol: Little Endian&lt;br/&gt;
C++ TBinaryProtocol: Big Endian&lt;br/&gt;
C++ TCompactProtocol: Little Endian&lt;br/&gt;
Python TBinaryProtocol: Big Endian&lt;br/&gt;
Python TCompactProtocol: Big Endian&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13742692" author="patrick.lawson" created="Fri, 16 Aug 2013 22:58:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached is a diff to fix cross compatibility between python and java TCompact doubles.  Note that this breaks compatibility between any python TCompact serialized without this patch applied.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
